,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">A different way LPUs could impr=
ove decode phase latencies is by accelerating a speculative decoding setup,=
 where we deploy draft models or Multi-Token Prediction (MTP) layers onto L=
PUs.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26=
px;font-size: 16px;">For a decoding step of context N tokens, adding k addi=
tional tokens during forward pass (a warm prefill of k new tokens) marginal=
ly increases the latency when k &lt;&lt; N. Using this property, speculativ=
e decoding uses a small draft model or MTP layers to predict k new tokens, =
saving time since small models have lower latency per decode step. To verif=
y the draft tokens, the main model only needs one warm prefill of k new tok=
ens, at the latency cost of roughly a single decode step. Speculative decod=
ing usually boosts output token per decode step by 1.5 to 2 tokens, dependi=
ng on the draft model / MTP accuracy. With its low latency capabilities, LP=
Us can further increase the latency savings and improve throughput.</p><div=
