 Groq&#8217;s own scaleup fabric. These connections are all via PCB trace, =
which necessitates an extremely high spec PCB to support this routing densi=
ty. This is why the belly-to-belly layout is used: it reduces the &#8216;X&=
#8217; and &#8216;Y&#8217; distance between all the LPUs and instead have r=
outing go in the &#8216;Z&#8217; dimension.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px=
