fy">The LPU also has 1x100G going to one FPGA, with each FPGA interfacing w=
ith 8 LPUs. The 2 FPGAs each have 8x PCIe Gen 5 going to the CPUs. The LPU =
needs to traverse through the FPGA to interface with the CPU as LPUs don&#8=
217;t have PCIe PHYs to interface directly.</p><h4 class=3D"header-anchor-p=
